  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CFD solver exposes tunable configuration parameters including base mesh element size (target 0.15 mm near impeller), turbulence model closure coefficients, and hemolysis power-law threshold stress. Validation results were obtained at the chosen settings for these parameters; however, no configuration binding node is provided and the deployment configuration is not constrained in the Context of Use.",
