    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for MRL 2. The six not-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 1. The CFD model demonstrates sufficient credibility to support identification of worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. Validation results obtained at the chosen configuration settings for mesh element size, turbulence closure coefficients, and hemolysis threshold parameter are judged adequate for the intended decision. The assessment team notes that these configuration parameters were not formally pinned or bound to a deployment configuration record, but considers this acceptable given the MRL 2 risk classification and the supporting test confirmation that reduces model influence to Medium.",
